Attribute buffer (cavern + Willy + guardians + items + portal)

The routine at #ADDR:0x870E# initialises this buffer with the contents of the
attribute buffer at #ADDR:0x5E00# (empty cavern), writes the attributes for Willy,
the guardians, the items and the portal into it, and then copies the result
to the attribute file.

Attribute buffer (empty cavern)

Initialised upon entry to a cavern by the routine at #ADDR:0x8684#, and updated by
the routines at #ADDR:0x8BBA# and #ADDR:0x9135#.

Screen buffer (cavern + Willy + guardians + items + portal)

The routine at #ADDR:0x870E# initialises this buffer with the contents of the
screen buffer at #ADDR:0x7000# (empty cavern), draws Willy, the guardians, the
items and the portal over this background, and then copies the result to the
display file.

Screen buffer (empty cavern)

Initialised upon entry to a cavern by the routine at #ADDR:0x8A75#, and updated by
the routines at #ADDR:0x8BBA#, #ADDR:0x9105# and #ADDR:0x9135#.

Cavern name

The cavern name is copied here and then used by the routine at #ADDR:0x8684#.

Cavern tiles

The cavern tiles are copied here by the routine at #ADDR:0x8684# and then used to
draw the cavern by the routine at #ADDR:0x8A75#.
.

Left-right movement table

Used by the routine at #ADDR:0x8BDD#. The entries in this table are used to map the
existing value (V) of Willy's direction and movement flags at #ADDR:0x806A# to a
new value (V'), depending on the direction Willy is facing and how he is
moving or being moved (by 'left' and 'right' keypresses and joystick input,
or by a conveyor).
.
One of the first four entries is used when Willy is not moving.
One of the next four entries is used when Willy is moving left.
One of the next four entries is used when Willy is moving right.

One of the final four entries is used when Willy is being pulled both left
and right; each entry leaves the flags at #ADDR:0x806A# unchanged (so Willy carries
on moving in the direction he's already moving, or remains stationary).
